<p>If I create a custom error in model:</p>  <pre><code>app/models/my_model.rb  class Person &lt; ActiveRecord::Base   def a_method_used_for_validation_purposes     errors.add(:name, "cannot contain the characters !@#%*()_-+=")   end end  person = Person.create(name: "!@#")  person.errors[:name]  # =&gt; ["cannot contain the characters !@#%*()_-+="]  person.errors.full_messages  # =&gt; ["Name cannot contain the characters !@#%*()_-+="] </code></pre>  <p>And make a create html method by <a href="https://github.com/drapergem/draper" rel="nofollow">draper</a>:</p>  <pre><code>app/decorators/my_decorator.rb  private def textarea(content)   content &lt;&lt; h.text_area(     "details",     object.question_number,     size: 300,     maxlength: 255,   )   content.html_safe end </code></pre>  <p>I want to raise a error if user didn't input a value from view. Then how can I catch that error in the decorator file? Is it possible?</p>